SOC Threat Intelligence Enrichment Tool

This is a Python-based simulation tool designed to mimic core workflows used in a Security Operations Center (SOC). The program analyzes log files, extracts IP addresses, and enriches them with simulated threat intelligence data to classify potential security risks.

# What the program does
Reads and processes raw log files line by line
Extracts IP addresses using regular expressions
Counts occurrences of each IP address
Matches IPs against a predefined threat intelligence database
Classifies each IP as:
Safe
Suspicious
Malicious
Unknown (if not found in the database)
Generates a structured security report in the terminal
# Purpose

The project is designed for educational purposes to demonstrate how SOC analysts:

Parse and analyze log data
Enrich raw security events with threat intelligence
Identify potentially malicious network activity
Prioritize security incidents based on risk level
⚙️ Technologies used
Python 3
Regular Expressions (regex)
Dictionaries for threat intelligence mapping
Basic data analysis logic
# Note

This tool does not connect to real threat intelligence services. It uses a simulated local dataset to demonstrate SOC-style analysis workflows.
